EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

Hh3cdot1sFormatStatus.name: Hh3cdot1sFormatStatus
Hh3cdot1sFormatStatus.description: Legacy means that the BPDU format is legacy. Dot1s means that the BPDU format is IEEE 802.1s. Auto means that the format of BPDU sending on the port is determined by the BPDU format of its connective port.

hh3cdot1sStpStatus.name: hh3cdot1sStpStatus
hh3cdot1sStpStatus.description: Whether the Bridge MSTP is enabled.

hh3cdot1sStpForceVersion.name: hh3cdot1sStpForceVersion
hh3cdot1sStpForceVersion.description: The mode of this Bridge spanning-tree protocol.

hh3cdot1sMstBridgeMaxHops.name: hh3cdot1sMstBridgeMaxHops
hh3cdot1sMstBridgeMaxHops.description: The maximum value of the Bridge hops.

hh3cdot1sMstMasterBridgeID.name: hh3cdot1sMstMasterBridgeID
hh3cdot1sMstMasterBridgeID.description: The Bridge Identifier of the current Master Bridge.

hh3cdot1sMstMasterPathCost.name: hh3cdot1sMstMasterPathCost
hh3cdot1sMstMasterPathCost.description: The CIST path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Master Bridge.

hh3cdot1sMstBpduGuard.name: hh3cdot1sMstBpduGuard
hh3cdot1sMstBpduGuard.description: Whether the Bridge BPDU Guard function is enabled. If the function is enabled, the port will shutdown when received BPDU and the port is configured as portfast.

hh3cdot1sMstAdminFormatSelector.name: hh3cdot1sMstAdminFormatSelector
hh3cdot1sMstAdminFormatSelector.description: The administrative Configuration Identifier Format Selector in use by the Bridge. This has a value of 0 indicate the format specified in the Standard of IEEE 802.1s.

hh3cdot1sMstOperFormatSelector.name: hh3cdot1sMstOperFormatSelector
hh3cdot1sMstOperFormatSelector.description: The operative Configuration Identifier Format Selector in use by the Bridge. This has a value of 0 indicate the format specified in the Standard of IEEE 802.1s.

hh3cdot1sMstOperConfigDigest.name: hh3cdot1sMstOperConfigDigest
hh3cdot1sMstOperConfigDigest.description: This MSTP Region's Configuration Digest Signature Key.

hh3cdot1sMstDefaultVlanAllo.name: hh3cdot1sMstDefaultVlanAllo
hh3cdot1sMstDefaultVlanAllo.description: Set default configuration about VLAN allocation and all VLANs are mapped to CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiBridgeID.name: hh3cdot1sMstiBridgeID
hh3cdot1sMstiBridgeID.description: The Bridge Identifier for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiBridgePriority.name: hh3cdot1sMstiBridgePriority
hh3cdot1sMstiBridgePriority.description: The Bridge Priority for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID. Step of 4096

hh3cdot1sMstiDesignedRoot.name: hh3cdot1sMstiDesignedRoot
hh3cdot1sMstiDesignedRoot.description: The Bridge Identifier of the Root Bridge for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiRootPathCost.name: hh3cdot1sMstiRootPathCost
hh3cdot1sMstiRootPathCost.description: The path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Root Bridge for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiRootPort.name: hh3cdot1sMstiRootPort
hh3cdot1sMstiRootPort.description: The Root Port for the spanning tree instance identified by the MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiRootType.name: hh3cdot1sMstiRootType
hh3cdot1sMstiRootType.description: Config this Bridge as a primary root or seconary root and or cancel the root for this spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiRemainingHops.name: hh3cdot1sMstiRemainingHops
hh3cdot1sMstiRemainingHops.description: The remaining hops of the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListLow.name: hh3cdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListLow
hh3cdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListLow.description: The lower part of administrative Vlan list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListHigh.name: hh3cdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListHigh
hh3cdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListHigh.description: The higher part of administrative Vlan list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListLow.name: hh3cdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListLow
hh3cdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListLow.description: The lower part of operative Vlan list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListHigh.name: hh3cdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListHigh
hh3cdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListHigh.description: The higher part of operative Vlan list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiPortIndex.name: hh3cdot1sMstiPortIndex
hh3cdot1sMstiPortIndex.description: The index of the Bridge Port

hh3cdot1sMstiState.name: hh3cdot1sMstiState
hh3cdot1sMstiState.description: The current state of the Port (i.e., Disabled, Discarding , Learning, Forwarding)

hh3cdot1sMstiPortPriority.name: hh3cdot1sMstiPortPriority
hh3cdot1sMstiPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) four bits of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of mstiPortIndex. And step of 16

hh3cdot1sMstiPathCost.name: hh3cdot1sMstiPathCost
hh3cdot1sMstiPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. The range of path cost is 1..65535 for 802.1d standard, is 1..200000000 for 802.1t standard, and is 1..200000 for the legacy standard.

hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedRoot.name: hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedRoot
hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedRoot.description: The Bridge Identifier of the Root Bridge for the port of the Spanning Tree instance identified by the MSTID

hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedCost.name: hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedCost
hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedBridge.name: hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedBridge
hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedPort.name: hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedPort
hh3cdot1sMstiDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

hh3cdot1sMstiMasterBridgeID.name: hh3cdot1sMstiMasterBridgeID
hh3cdot1sMstiMasterBridgeID.description: The Bridge Idnetifier of the current Master Bridge. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiMasterPortCost.name: hh3cdot1sMstiMasterPortCost
hh3cdot1sMstiMasterPortCost.description: The CIST path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Master Bridge. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortEdgeport.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortEdgeport
hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortEdgeport.description: Whether the port fast is enabled. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint
hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint.description: Whether the port conects the point to point link. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpMcheck.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpMcheck
hh3cdot1sMstiStpMcheck.description: Forcing the state machine to send MST BPDUs in this manner can be used to test whether all legacy Bridges on a given LAN have been removed. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpTransLimit.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpTransLimit
hh3cdot1sMstiStpTransLimit.description: The value used by the Port Transmit state machine to limit the maximum transmission rate. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXStpBPDU.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXStpBPDU
hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXStpBPDU.description: The number of received Config BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXStpBPDU.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXStpBPDU
hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXStpBPDU.description: The number of transimitted Config BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXTCNBPDU.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXTCNBPDU
hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXTCNBPDU.description: The number of received TCN BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXTCNBPDU.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXTCNBPDU
hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXTCNBPDU.description: The number of transimitted TCN BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXRSTPBPDU.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXRSTPBPDU
hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXRSTPBPDU.description: The number of received RST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU
hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU.description: The number of transimitted RST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXMSTPBPDU.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXMSTPBPDU
hh3cdot1sMstiStpRXMSTPBPDU.description: The number of received MST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXMSTPBPDU.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXMSTPBPDU
hh3cdot1sMstiStpTXMSTPBPDU.description: The number of transimitted MST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpClearStatistics.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpClearStatistics
hh3cdot1sMstiStpClearStatistics.description: Clear the spanning tree statistic. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpStatus.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpStatus
hh3cdot1sMstiStpStatus.description: Whether the spanning tree protocol is enabled on this port. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiPortRootGuard.name: hh3cdot1sMstiPortRootGuard
hh3cdot1sMstiPortRootGuard.description: Whether the root guard is enabled. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiPortLoopGuard.name: hh3cdot1sMstiPortLoopGuard
hh3cdot1sMstiPortLoopGuard.description: Whether the loop protection is enabled. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType
hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType.description: Type of BPDU which the port is sending.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint
hh3cdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint.description: This object indicates whether the port has connected to a point-to-point link or not. The value of the node is an operative value. The administrative value can be read from the node hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint. If the value of hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is auto, the value of this node should be calculated by the network topology of this port. If the value of hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is forceFalse, the value of this node is false. If the value of hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is forceTrue, the value of this node is true.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt
hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt.description: The value of the node is an administrative value. Value legacy means that the MST BPDU format is forced to legacy. Value dot1s means that the MST BPDU format is forced to IEEE 802.1s. Value auto means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is determined by the MST BPDU that the port has received. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt.name: hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt
hh3cdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt.description: The format of MST BPDU which the port is sending. Value legacy means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is legacy. Value dot1s means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is IEEE 802.1s. Effective in CIST.

hh3cdot1sStpPathCostStandard.name: hh3cdot1sStpPathCostStandard
hh3cdot1sStpPathCostStandard.description: Path cost standard of the bridge. Value dot1d-1998 is IEEE 802.1d standard in 1998, value dot1t is IEEE 802.1t standard, and value legacy is a private legacy standard.

hh3cPortMstiStateForwarding.name: hh3cPortMstiStateForwarding
hh3cPortMstiStateForwarding.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a port turns into forwarding state form other state.

hh3cPortMstiStateDiscarding.name: hh3cPortMstiStateDiscarding
hh3cPortMstiStateDiscarding.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a port turns into discarding state form forwarding state.

hh3cBridgeLostRootPrimary.name: hh3cBridgeLostRootPrimary
hh3cBridgeLostRootPrimary.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the bridge is no longer the root bridge of the instance. Another switch with higher priority has already been the root bridge of the instance.

hh3cPortMstiRootGuarded.name: hh3cPortMstiRootGuarded
hh3cPortMstiRootGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a root-guard port receives a superior message on the relevant instance.

hh3cPortMstiBpduGuarded.name: hh3cPortMstiBpduGuarded
hh3cPortMstiBpduGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an edged port of the BPDU-guard switch recevies BPDU packets.

hh3cPortMstiLoopGuarded.name: hh3cPortMstiLoopGuarded
hh3cPortMstiLoopGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an Alternate-Port or Root-Port is aged out.
